# Hustronix Design Rules (Hard Constraint)

Every visual must communicate **one strategic insight**.

If the visual is beautiful but does not increase understanding, **reject it**.

```text
Clarity > Creativity
Understanding > Decoration
Signal > Aesthetics
```

## Visual DNA

```yaml
brand:
  name: Hustronix
  tagline: "Decide. Align. Execute."
  style:
    - Strategic
    - Technical
    - Minimal
    - Executive
  avoid:
    - Cartoon
    - Illustration-heavy
    - Startup hype
    - Bright gradients
    - Generic AI art
```

## Colors (NO additional colors allowed)

| Token | Hex | Use |
|-------|-----|-----|
| primary_white | #EDEDED | Typography |
| primary_black | #0A0A0A | Default background |
| signal_gold | #D4AF37 | Accent, logo NIX, lines |
| muted_gold | #A88F2A | Secondary accent |
| dark_grey | #1A1A1A | Cards, panels |
| soft_grey | #9CA3AF | Body secondary text |

Default layout: black background (#0A0A0A), white typography (#EDEDED), signal gold accents (#D4AF37).

## Logo System

Assets in `assets/brand/`:

| File | Use |
|------|-----|
| logo-lockup.png | Official full lockup — CTA slides |
| logo-horizontal.png | Official horizontal — content slide footers |
| logo-icon.svg | Legacy vector mark (fallback) |
| logo-lockup.svg | Legacy vector lockup (fallback) |
| hex-grid.svg | Subtle background texture |
| tokens.css | Slide CSS variables |

Tagline lockup: **DECIDE. ALIGN. EXECUTE.** — embedded in `logo-lockup.png`.

Clearspace: radius of the central gold circle in the logo mark.

## Typography

- **Primary font:** Inter only (Light, Regular, Medium, SemiBold, Bold)
- Slide headline: Bold 52–64px
- Slide body: Regular 26px, soft grey
- Labels: SemiBold uppercase, signal gold, letter-spaced

**Forbidden:** Poppins, Montserrat, Playfair, any decorative font.

## Brand Icons (line art, gold)

| Icon | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| Signal | Node network — Intelligence |
| System | Hexagon — Structure |
| Decision | Crosshair — Choice point |
| Execution | Arrow — Forward motion |

Visual narrative flow: Inputs → Intelligence → Decision → Execution

## Slide Format

- Size: **1080×1080** (LinkedIn carousel)
- Background: deep black + hex grid overlay at ~35% opacity
- Footer: logo icon + HUSTRO/NIX wordmark on every slide
- Slide index: `01 / 06` in gold (top left)

## Generate Carousels

```bash
python scripts/generate_carousel.py --idea-id 3
python scripts/generate_carousel.py --option 1
python scripts/generate_carousel.py --idea-id 3 --single
python scripts/render_carousel.py assets/generated/3/
```

Slack: `carousel 1` | `carousel 2` | `carousel 3`

Output: `assets/generated/{id}/slides/*.png` + `preview.html`

**Quality tier:** Premium v2 — 7 layout types (cover, split, pipeline, flow, stats, quote, cta)

## Visual Categories

| # | Category | Structure | When |
|---|----------|-----------|------|
| 1 | decision_pattern | Trigger → Decision → Outcome → Lesson | Most common |
| 2 | strategic_question | Large typography, minimal | Question-led posts |
| 3 | founder_insight | Large quote + small framework | Interview content |
| 4 | execution_model | Flowchart, hexagons, signal network | Framework posts |
| 5 | future_of_organizations | Cinematic, still minimal | Vision/category |

## Design Score Thresholds

Reject if ANY fail:
- clarity < 8
- brand_consistency < 9
- founder_appeal < 8
- di_alignment < 9
- generic_ai_feel > 2

Use `python scripts/score_design.py` to record scores.

## Output Protocol

1. Classify visual category
2. Generate YAML design brief (NOT raw image prompt)
3. Write to `assets/generated/{draft_id}/design-brief.yaml`
4. Score brief before any image generation
5. Only generate images after design score passes

Never call image generation without a scored YAML brief first.
